Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
#lid{}. Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the
boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve
(the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Cut the @cauliflower{1} into florets (like small trees), halving any large ones.

Pop the cauliflower onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{},
season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread them out in
a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden brown and tender,
about ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the cauli roasts, trim the @pak choi{1}, then thinly slice widthways.

Trim the @cucumber{1}, then pop onto a #cutting board{} and use a
#rolling pin{} to gently smack it a few times until split. Cut into roughly
2cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

When the cauliflower has 5 mins left, drizzle over the @gochujang paste{50%g},
half the @honey{15%g} and half the @sesame oil{10%ml}. Gently toss to coat the
florets evenly.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Return to the oven for the remaining time until tender.

== Dressing and Pak Choi ==

In the meantime, in a #medium bowl{}, combine the @rice vinegar{15%ml},
@soy sauce{15%ml} and the remaining @honey{15%g} and @sesame oil{10%ml}. Add the
cucumber to the bowl and toss in the dressing.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the pak choi and stir-fry until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds} more, then remove from the heat and
set aside.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your
#bowls{}.

Top with the gochujang cauliflower, smacked cucumber (and dressing) and pak
choi in separate sections.

Sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} to finish.

Enjoy!